    <stitle>CAB: 7000 AND 8000 SERIES MODELS - ADJUSTMENTS - STRIKER PIN</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="x16029204" svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="1">
        <title>STRIKER PIN</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>Adjustment procedures show driver side; passenger side procedures are the same.</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Striker pin procedures are the same for either front or rear cab doors.</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f1603855" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg16/g1603855.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 150. Striker Pin</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. DOOR LOCK PILLAR</callout1>
                <callout1>2. BOLT</callout1>
                <callout1>3. STRIKER PIN</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slightly loosen bolts securing striker pin to door lock pillar.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Move striker pin as required at the door lock pillar to obtain proper door fit and latching
                position.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Hold striker pin in place and tighten both bolts at the cab door lock pillar. Tighten bolts
                to 19 to 24 Lbf-ft (26 to 32 N&#8226;m).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Close door and check for proper fit. If further adjustment is required, repeat procedure.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
